\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Can you just tell me your name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Emmaline Gladys May Peck.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 119, Marsh Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 And you are married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes. Widow, I'm a widow. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 And the year of your marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 1925.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Year of birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 1899.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 And your birthplace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Luton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Can you give me the address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Well it was - a street called North Street. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 How many years did you live in that house where you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 About - twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 And where did you live then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Then we went to live in Telbot Road. My people bought a house in Telbot Road.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What year would that bring you up to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 About - nearly 19 - 13 I think.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 How long did you stay in Telbot Road?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Until I was married. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Do you remember why you moved from North Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes, quite well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Can you tell me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Well it was in November, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Why did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
Well - in those days they were quite small houses and my mother had got four children you see, and they bought this house, it was a bigger house altogether. Better house, yes, on the outskirts. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 How many brothers and sisters,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 I have one brother and two sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 How old was your father when you were born, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 He was married at twenty-four, and I think they waited two years for my sister, and then two
 years for me, that would bring him about to twenty-eight, wouldn't it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Where did he come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Luton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 He was a Luton man was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 And what was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Hand sewn shoemaker. Yes. A bespoke - hand sewn shoemaker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did he have another job before or after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 No, he did that all his life from when he was about twelve until he retired at about seventy-two. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did he ever have any casual or part time jobs as well as that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 No, only he served in the - first world war - for a year or two in the Air Force. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Do you remember him being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 No, never. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Do you know how old your mother was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 My mother was about - she was four years younger than my father. So that would make her about twenty-four. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Where did she come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Luton. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did she have any jobs before she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes, she had an - a hat factory of her own before she was married. They used to be small factories an
d - lots of people had them you know and used to work them - just one or two - people helping them you know. Then they used to take the hats into the town, to sell them. She had one of those. Then after she was married she used to do - work for someone el
se at home. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Hat work still was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes. Machining, yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What sort of hours would she have put into that after she was married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Oh I don't think she ever started before lunchtime. She used to see to all the work in the house, a
nd then - clear up and sort of start about two I think in the afternoon. And she'd probably be on and off, until about eight at night. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 I suppose if she was doing it at home she could see to you at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Oh yes, she was never away fr
om home, she never left us. No. And we used to take the work all - all the - manufacturer, which were relatives of hers that she'd set up in businesses and helped you know. And they used to either bring it or we used to take it backwards and forwards you 
know. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Which house do you remember best, do you remember the Old Street house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes, I remember it very well, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 You were there until you were twelve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes, twelve or thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 How many rooms were there in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 There was only four - five. Five rooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Can you describe them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
Yes, it was like a four - roomed house, with a porch and an - and an out house like a - a larger kitchen, with benches and - and then a cloakroom in between. And only two bedrooms then there was. Only two bedrooms, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 And downstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Two rooms, and the - out - this big place at the - kitchen, it was - we'd call it a kitchen now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What were the other two rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 One was a - where we used to eat and my mother used to
 have her machine. And the other one was a front room, we used to call them - front rooms or parlours in those days you know, where you had the piano and the suite and the - the parties you know and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 That was for best was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Where did father do his work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
Well he was - apprenticed under his own father, which was a - hand sewing shoemaker all his life, and he had his own business, a small one man business. And he used to work for him until he was - about sixteen I should i
magine, and then he went to a place in Upper George Street called Skeltons, where he had a shop, and used to take in - customer's work, and then my father used to work on the premises - and - go from morning 'til evening, and then - when his father died, 
a
nd the business was sold - the money had to be divided between about six children, so he paid - the money to buy his father's business which he carried on, because the others had to share the money. - And from then on until he retired he worked in his own
 place. And then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Was that far from home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
No. We had a private house and this was - this was my grandfather's house with his business. In the meantime - during the - it would be the first world war - I think he must have left his place, or the m
an must have given up or something, because he went to work for a firm in London, in - Bond Street. And there they used to send all the work to Luton - and he used to make - well all - people like - he - he made Lord Beaverbrook, Princess Alice - Alice o 
M
ila - of - Atholone, and lots of American - actresses that used to come over here which was - an unheard of thing in those days, and they used to order about thirteen pairs. Dance shoes, pumps, evening shoes, brocade shooting shoes, and my father used to 
have - about - half of those to do, all the superb shoes, and another man that worked in Luton used to do the brogues and the - stouter - type of shoe. And they were great friends you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did your father go up to London often then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes, he use
d to go up to London very often. But they sent all the work down by post. Yes. And - he used to - have all the stuff sent to make complete shoes, and before he started when - I could make them because I've seen them done - over the years with my grandfath
er and my father, and then my son started you know when he - when he was about fourteen, started making his own. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did father make shoes for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes, he made all of our shoes, we always had lovely shoes and boots. High legged boots you know.
 And we used to go skating, we'd always got boots up her. Yes. Patent here, and kid at the top, all laced up you know. Yes, he used to make us lovely shoes. And his own shoes he used to make - so light, that if he - when he went into the Arm - into the Ai
r
force he couldn't wear the shoes, he took his own shoes and used to fold them up, like an envelope and put one in one pocket and one in the other, they were so light, hand made you know. And everyone used to admire my mother's shoes, even in - trains or o
n holidays people used to sit and look at her shoes and ask her - where she got them from you know, it was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 He must have been a marvellous person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 He was a marvellous man, and he had - he was offered a job at the hospital when they started doing
 - patients work, and he never earned much money, because - in London, I think it was about five pounds a pair he would get for making, but he couldn't make above two pair a week. And just as he had this good job offered him at the hospital, he thought of
 
retiring, he was too old. Well that's the sort of job he would have loved, because he used to make cripples shoes, cripples and deformed people, cork - inches and inches of cork to build up, and steel bars through, and all that type - beautiful work, and 
all the cripples - that's anybody in Luton and district used to - go to him. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 He was well known in Luton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 He's well known, very well known.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did anyone else live in the house besides your parents and your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Sisters and brother isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 One brother, yes, two sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did you ever have relations to stay or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Not to sleep, we used to have a lot of company. And if my mother and father ever went anywhere - and stayed - for a weekend or overnig
ht, which they used to do, when we were all four quite young, and - we always had an aunt and an uncle come to sleep in, in my mother's bed and look after us for the two or three days. And my mother used to do it for them. People used to help each other o
ut like that in olden times you know, different to what they do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did mother ever pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes. Yes. She used to have a - a regular help. In fact - the man that helped - the man that worked at the same place as my fathe
r - had a lovely daughter - that used to - my mother used to pay her one and six a week to come an look after us - four children, and she used to take us out and - you know - sort of - I think she used to help my mother wash up or something like that. And
 one and six was quite a lot of money in those days you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What about the housework, who did that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Oh my mother always did that, she always kept her home beautiful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 This girl came every day did she, did she come all day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 She came - 
oh no, she was at school I think. I think she used to come in the evenings and Saturday mornings and - take us to Sunday school Sundays and all like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 How did you get on with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Very well, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 You liked her?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What did she call your mother, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 I don't remember. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What did you call her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 We used to call her Annie. Annie. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 And she called you by your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 hristian name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Well - m
y mother - used to have bronchitis very badly, and she mostly had her washing done out. I can remember the time when she was up at four in the morning washing, and she was like me, she used to love washing, but when she was ill and couldn't do it - she us
e
d to - you know, there were one - there was a - an aunt, that we used to have to take all the washing to, she - she did it for a time, and then there was a woman lived near us in Telbot Road, that used to come and fetch it and do it every week at one time
 I remember. Mm. And I've done it when she's been ill. Mm. Right up until I was married I was always washing and - cooking when she was ill. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did she make any clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 She made all of our clothes and her own. Yes, everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 And father made the shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did you ever have any second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 hand clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
No, I don't think so, but I do think - we had an aunt - that used to give my mother - clothes, I don't think my mother altered them for us but I can remember her cutting them up and making rugs with them and all things like that. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did you ever have any new clothes that mother didn't make, that you'd go to the shop to buy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 No, we had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120  tailor}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 made clothes made - when we were getting on for about - thirteen or fourte
en. My mother used to have a tailoress that used to make - my sister and I - things alike, like a little dress and little coat, and - ever so expensive, I've seen my mother sit down and cry over the bill. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Why did she do it then do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Well - she always liked to see us look nice and - she always - tried to look nice herself. But she was a lovely dressmaker. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 She didn't have much time did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 It's amazing how they used to get the work in. I think she sat up - I've known h
er to sit up on Saturday evenings - finishing silk dresses for me and my sister, and trimming hats - and ironing her silk gloves, and even making my friend hats and dresses to go to some do at the chapel, and she's sat up until midnight, but if they wasn'
t done at midnight she wouldn't finish - finish them on Sunday. No. No, she wasn't deeply religious but she'd got her convictions and she wouldn't let us do anything on Sunday. Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did father help around the house at all with jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 He used to - wallpaper the walls and paint. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 How about washing up or cooking or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
Yes, I've known him do - vegetables for her. And if she wasn't well but - he was no man to be domesticated. But he always had a garden, and a piece of shooting ground that he used to go out and shoot - for rabbits and hares. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Would that be land belonging to somebody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes, that he - he used to belong to farm - to a farmer, and for about - I'd don't know how much, I suppose a pound or 
two a year or something like that, him and his father used to rent it. Then they used to go off with the guns every Sunday morning and - Christmas and - holidays. And they always had allotment gardens where they used to grow all the vegetables and they us
ed to grow beautiful flowers, used to show in the flower shows. Yes, my father used to win - cups and medals, gold medals, and carvers and all sorts of beautiful things. Showing flowers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did he do the fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 He'd always - always - he always set the fire going in the morning, and always cleared the fire out. Always got the coal in. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 How about repairs and improvements to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Well it wasn't our own house you see, it was a - a small house and it was a nice little house, but I thi
nk they only used to pay about six and six a week rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did the landlord do repairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
And - no, in those days they didn't you know. No. And I think that's why my mother - you know, she wanted a place of her own. Where they could - well more room for one thing, and - a better and bigger house you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did you have any jobs you had to do regularly at home to help out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 I used to wash up. And my mother, when she did hats - we were never made to do them 
but we were always sort of - coaxed somehow into doing them. Or treated you know. My father would say, you know, you do this, you do that, I'll buy you - a few oranges or - something you know. And - when my mother used to do hats I always did what they ca
ll the centres. You had to start off with the plait the right way, do a little twist and work it round to about as big as a ha'penny, into what they called the centre of the crown, my mother used to give me three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 pence a dozen for doing those. I used to do 
a dozen, or two dozen every night. Which used to take me about an hour or two. It was a long job because that was the main - if the centre and the button was nice, that made a nice beginning to the hat, then my mother used to machine round them then, she 
was a perfect machinist. Mm. She could sit and machine - and put it on the block and it was just as though - it had been blocked on the block, and she very rarely made a mistake you know. It was experience you know, over the years, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 When he was home did your father help with you children, dressing or undressing you or bathing you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
Yes, he used to help bath us and - used to brush our hair, and - he - when we'd finished he used to sit in his armchair and we had to brush his and curl his hair, and - fuss us about you know like. Yes, he was ever such an affectionate man. Mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did he read to you at all, tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 No, I think my mother used to read to us. My father used to help us do competitions. He always encouraged us - encour
aged us - to do competitions.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What sort?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
Well, it - there used to be John Bull and - Tit-Bits and all those things and - you know, he used to send them in through the post. I don't think they ever won a sausage as far as I know. But - used to enjoy doing it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did father ever take you out without mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
Only - backwards and forwards to work, when we went out to work. He always escorted us back to work, my sister and I, and he used to say to us, if you'll back with me, I'll buy you
 - he'd either buy us an ice cream on the way, or an apple or an orange or whatever we wanted. But he was so proud, he used to love us to walk with him, one each side, and then drop him off at his shop, and us continue on, you know, yes. But I don't think
 
he ever took us out on his own, mother and dad used to - take us to Harpenden to the relatives - on Sundays you know and take us to the fete, we were always all together, and always go for walks together, all six of us. Probably relations as well you know
. Used to go all round the country and - go to his shooting ground picking violets, and all things like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did he ever look after you if mother was out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 She was never out. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 He could have done is she had been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 He could have done I expect, she was never out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did you carry on those jobs around the house after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 And your brother and sister as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Well, I used to do most because they always looked on me - they used to call 
me the old warhorse, because during the war I used to queue for the meat, do the washing, and when they were all ill and I was all right I used to nurse them and look after them. Yes, and I used to seem to - sort of - run the house for weeks on end at a t
ime. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 But did they help around the house too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
I think they used to, yes, but - I used to do most of the work, yes. I suppose I used to stick me neck out and do it because I liked it, I think you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did you help them with things like dressing and undressing them when they were very little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
No, I think my mother used to do all that you know. Yes. Don't ever remember doing anything for the - little ones, cos I was quite young when the other two - there was only about six years between us. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did they help you in any way do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 No, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What about bedtime, were you expected to go to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Oh yes, we all had to be in bed by eight o'clock. Yes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120 
. All washed and dressed and sup}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 pered and - kissed, and all to bed by eight o'clock. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did mother put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
Yes, she used to put us to bed, we had a dolls house and a fire in the bedroom, and she didn't mind if we played. We used to play tins on the wall to the neighbours children,
 in code, you know, tap, tiddle, tap tap and messages and all that. She didn't mind as long as we settled down after a time and went to sleep. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 You had a fire in the bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Used to have a fire in the bedroom. And a big dolls house you know and - mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Do you remember what age you put yourself to bed without mother helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
Oh I should imagine - when the boys was born. Or when the youngest girl was born. I don't - I don't know because I can remember when we were - fif - when I was fi
fteen and sixteen - my mother'd come in an tuck us up. Yes. After we moved up to the other house. It was very cold, it was on the hill and a - a very open - part of the town. No houses beyond us, we were sort of right on the edge of the town then, now - i
t's called near the centre of the town. It's only about - just a mile away from the centre of the town, and that was all fields when we were young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 You must have shared a bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Oh yes, we all - well, up until we moved - up until we moved, thre
e of us - shared the bedroom, there used to be my sister and I in one bed, it was a huge room, and we used to have our bed there and my brother's bed was over the other side. I don't remember muc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120 h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120  about it but after we moved - he used to have a room on his own and - and we had a room.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 So mother and father would have one bedroom and then you children in the other one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What about bathing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 We used to - we - there was no bathrooms in those days. Every Friday night - grandfather us
ed to come round - and we all used to have a bath in front of the fire one after the other in a huge bath, in front of the fire. Then my mother used to cook - a pailful of chitlings, chitlings, yes, you never see them now, but they could buy them, we - I 
u
sed to go to the shop and fetch them. You could get what they called a set of chitterlings for about one and eleven. And that was a pailful, of all - inside of - don't know whether it was pigs or cows or what. And then my mother used to clean them all out
, and scrub them, and cook them, and then we used to have chitterlings and pease pudding and my grandfather always come round to see all this going on. Friday nights.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did you look forward to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Well I don't know whether we did or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 How about clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
Oh - always got clean clothes. Beautiful - white pinafores my mother used to make us, with all lace on and - she used to starch them, we was always - clean. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Where did you have your meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 We had our meals - in the
 winter we used to have it in the - in the - well - not the front room but the kitchen, what we used to call the kitchen then. But in the summer, we used to have it in this other room, because it was a huge room with the windows opened out into the garden
, and the windows were always open and I think we used to have it in there then. But only in the summertime. In the winter we always had it in the - in the other room, in the middle room like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did you ever have anything in the front room?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 We used to have parties and - snack meals in there you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 For special occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Where did mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Mother always cooked in the - in the back kitchen, what we called the back kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What did she cook on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 On a gas stove. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What time did you have breakfast, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
Well, I used to be an early riser. And I used to get up, mostly at six o'clock - and I used to go with a friend of mine that used to come whistle up the passage for me, and we use
d to go to the garden, pinch a stick of rhubarb, and wait for my father to come about seven, and then we used to go back home which was about a good ten minutes or more walk, right through a sort of park, and we used to go home then and have our breakfast
 then. Then I used to go shopping for my mother before I went to school. Used to go and fetch the meat, and all things like that, before I went to school, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What about the other members of the family, would they all have breakfast together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 No, I think we all had it together. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Do you remember what you had for breakfast? To eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
Well - in those days - we used to have either - bacon or bacon and egg, not every morning, but most weekends, and - meat, we used to fry meat and
 stuff like that. Yes. Yes. After I was married we had - steak - every Sunday morning. My husband and I did, yes, for years. A pound of rump steak between us, and do you know how much that was a pound then, one and four a pound. Yes. 'Course we wasn't ear
ning the money or handling the money, my stray cat come again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What did you drink at breakfast time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
Tea I think. Mm. We always had plenty of bread and butter, and home made jam and home made marmalade and stuff like that. My mother used to make to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120 ns and tons of - cupboards full}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120  of this stuff. And we'd always got plenty of that sort of thing you know. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 How about midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Always had a good cooked midday meal. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What sort of things would you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 We used to have - S
undays we always had a joint of beef with Yorkshire, roas potatoes, and - in those days there weren't tinned fruit when we were little. I can remember tinned fruit coming in. Yes. But we always - grew fruit, we had - fruit trees, and you could always - bu
y fruit of some sort from somewhere. And we always had fruit and custard and stuff like that. My mother wouldn't buy tinned stuff when it first came in. She always used to pr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120 
eserve her own. Bottle p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 lum - plums, so did I, I used to bottle - plums, blackcurrants, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120 gooseberries}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 , which my mother always did when we were young you know, we always had - plenty of fresh fruit. Plenty of green vegetables. All home grown stuff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 How about the weekday main meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 We used to have - on Monday we always had - wha
t was left from Sunday hotted up. And always a nice cup of tea afterwards. Then Tuesday we'd perhaps have what we called dumplings. That was suet roll with meat and onions and things inside, with mashed potatoes or whole potatoes and greens or - cauliflow
e
rs or peas, whatever there was going, and perhaps a jam roly poly. Then we'd have pie one day. One day we'd have - stew, lamb stew, with a - what my mother called a light pudding, made of suet and cooked in a cloth. Then she'd cut slices off. And if there
 was enough left you could have another slice with jam on. I do that now sometimes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What about evening meal, did you have an evening meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 We always had a good tea. Always had a good tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What time of day would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 We us
ed to have that when we all came out of school, about half past four. It was always ready, ready set on the table and we used to take our friends in, they were always welcome. Bread and butter and jam and - always home made cake, my mother used to make a 
lot of fruit cake and - stuff like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What about after that, did you have anything else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes, we used to have supper. Yes, we always had what we liked for supper.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What sort of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Well either porridge or - bread and butter and jam, or toast or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 And a drink did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 And a drink, yes, always had a drink. I think mostly - tea or cocoa it used to be in those days you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 So you ate well didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes we did, we had a jolly good living, I should imagine we had as good living as the Queen of England. We did have a good living. Mm.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did your mother make any bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes. Yes. So do I. Sometimes. Not so much now 'cos I'm here on me own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did she always make it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 No,
 no, we had a lovely baker lived near us, that used to bake - oh it was all hand made bread in those days and - scones and - cheese cakes, and - what did my mother used to love, cream puffs, you know, and things like that. But we mostly only had those Sat
u
rdays. Sundays we always had cream in our tea Sunday morning, my mother used to have a - can of cream, only used to be about a shilling in those days, enough to go all round, couple of spoonfuls of cream. And the milkman used to live up - straight opposit
e where we lived. So all we had to do was just go over - can of cream, and back for breakfast. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did mother ever make any pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What about wines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Wine, heaps and heaps of wine we've made, all sorts. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What about medicine, did she have any of her own favourite remedies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
Yes, oh - yes, oh yes, we had to have our brimstone and treacle every Friday night. Brimstone. Used to be like a yellow sulphury looking powder, with a spoonful of treacle in, stirred in, thic
k, and we all had to have about half or a teaspoonful - Friday night.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What was that supposed to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
Well supposed to keep your bowels working and keep your - skin - nice, my mother used to say, you know. She used to make her own cough mixture. 
Yes. She used to make - well I don't remember, it was - she used to have it written down on a paper, and she used to make it for other people too, they used to love it and it was jolly good stuff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 I wonder what she put in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 I don't know. And -
 when we lived up Talbot Road in the first world war, we had officers billeted with us, the regiments were - billeted all in the street below us, and there was just our four houses had the officers. And - one of them - well he had a tickling cough and he 
c
ame in hm hm one night, he said - wondered if - my mother could - he knew we'd got this - medicine, if she could give him anything for it. And she gave him it, they were thrilled to bits and it done them good. Yes, and they were people with money. Mm. Yes
.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 I wonder what it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 I forget now, it was - she used to put black treacle in it - and - it was - oh it was dark, a dark looking stuff you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did she get stuff from the chemist for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Oh yes, we used to go and buy it at the chemist, I can't think what it was called now, li}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120 qu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 orice, I think there was lic - li}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120 qu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 orice in it, piece of li}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120 qu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 orice, you used to buy - black li}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120 qu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 orice in them days in little - hard sticks. Believe she used to crush it and put that in. And I think it had got a beaten egg in it. And - }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120 chlordane}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 . Something like }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120 chlordane}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 . And this black treacle. It used to be good stuff, mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did father and mother make any beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 No they - I don't think - well they used to make - there used to be some stuff - when we
 were very young that you could - buy from - I think it was Boots, they used to call it bees wine. And you could buy this stuff and make sort of fizzy beer. But my mother and father were never beery people. They'd have a bottle of wine, you know, at Chris
tmas, but they weren't - not what you'd call drinking people. They didn't disappro}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120 ve of it, they'd have fa - bott}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
le of stout if anyone came or - anything like that, but they weren't drinkers. In those days lots of people were - heavy drinkers. But - I suppose really they couldn't afford it and they never just sort of indulged in it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did you have any livestock at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes, we had cats and dogs and birds. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did you have anything to eat, like pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 My grandfather used to keep a pig on his allotment. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Chickens at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Chickens, yes, we - my mother and father used to keep chickens. We always had - our own eggs. Yes, used to keep pure bre}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 ds - used to be - Light Sussex what they used to keep, whitey birds with speckles, yes
. Lovely - oh yes, we had lovely chickens - to eat, you know, we used to eat them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Any goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
Goat, no. No. But I'll tell you what else my mother used to buy, there used to be a woman lived about - in the country, about a mile or two from where 
we lived that used to bring very often on a Friday - three dozen starlings. Cook - ready to cook, skinned and feathered, looking exactly like little - pigeons, all laid on a plate, thirty-six of 'em, and I think they used to be three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 pence a dozen, used to cost my mother nine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
pence. And she used to do this because this woman needed the money. And this woman used to do all this work with these little birds, now I couldn't eat them. When she made - what's it - starling pie I think they used to call it, I woul
dn't eat it. No, I wouldn't eat it. And she used to cook bullocks heart, stuffed, and I wouldn't eat that. No. I used to fetch them, and my mother used to stuff them, but I just couldn't somehow. Mm. She used to scold me you know, say, you'll be glad to e
at anything one day, and I - I was. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 There probably wasn't any poaching done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 No. He'd got - he had a licence and shooting rights, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Do you remember mother having less food so the family could have a bit more, did she ever go without?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
Well - she was the type of woman that if there wasn't much to go round she would have gone without. But I don't think she ever really went - short, you know. I don't think she ever - was in as bad state, you know what I mean, no I don't ever remember.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did father have bigger helpings than the rest of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Well we all had good appetites I can remember. We all had great plateful of food, and we used to eat it. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes. Providing we wer
en't quarrelling or cheeky. My father'd never allow us to be - quarrelsome. He'd put one in one room and one in the other 'til you left off. Yes. And - never to be cheeky, I always remember saying something cheeky to my mother once, only once, I think I w
a
s about - thirteen or fourteen or fifteen, I know I wasn't very old and he just gave me one look, and he said, don't you speak like that to your mother. And you just sort of froze up and that was - that was the last time you did. Mind you, I think if the 
children day was brought up a little stricter, we was never - cruelly treated, never - ill-treated, but we always had to take notice. And abide by the rules, and if I think younger children - were done - if that was done}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120  to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120  them more now there wouldn't be t
he - delinquents about as there are. But you see - in those days almost everybody's children were disciplined. Well now everybody's children are not disciplined, so it wouldn't do for one family to be - to have a disciplined family that's got to mix with 
others, because there'd be - trod on. Mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 When food was served were you allowed to choose what you wanted to eat or did you have to have a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Well we didn't have to be too fussy. No. My mother wouldn't go out and buy something
 different for us, but she'd always got a choice of something, you know, you weren't made to do anything, you were well talked into - into trying to get you to, but if she really saw that you didn't like anything, you know, she would always - give you som
ething else. But, she would never - make a business to say, I've got to buy one this and one the other. She used to say no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What about leaving food on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 We never left anything I don't think. Never remember any of us ever leaving anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
If you wanted something that was on the table, like the salt, did you have to ask for it to be passed to you or did you just reach and help yourself to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Well I think it was always in the middle of the table, you know, and - I think we used 
to say, would you pass the salt, you know, to one or the other of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 How about holding the knife and fork, did you have to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Oh yes, we had to sit properly and behave, yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Could you bring a toy or book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 No, no I think my mother would say you put that down and come and have your meal. You know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Well we always used to say, can we get down mother or - something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did you have to wait until they'd finished theirs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 No, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes, mostly all together, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did you have the same places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes,
 always our own place. Yes, and I always had my own knife and fork and spoon, I would never have anybody else's. I was always in trouble over that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Who served the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 My mother. She always - made it, dished it up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Was it dished up in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Always dished up in the kitchen and brought in on the plates yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 In what order were you served, who was served first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Well I think my dad was. And then the children. Or if we were home from school first I suppose we had ours - first you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Do you remember where the younger children sat before they were old enough to sit up to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Used to have a chair, high chair with a - front piece on it you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Where would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 By the side of the fire. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Who fed them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 My mother. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 This girl who came to help out, did she ever eat with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes, sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did she eat at the same table as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes. And she used to take us to her house, to her mother and father's. we used to
 go there to tea and - and to to the weddings, any - anything going on yes, we were - family friends. She was always looked on as the - well, not the maid, but it was always - you had to see Annie if you wanted to do anything or - yes, she - she was in ch
arge, yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 My mother? Yes. Very shy. But - she was very shy, but oh yes, she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did she show affection to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes. Every such an affectionate mum. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 If you had any worries could you share them with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
Well I think we were too sensitive. I can remember lots of things that I wished I could have said to my mother, but it wasn't because she wouldn't have listened. I think we were all shy. And shy of each other. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What about father, could you talk to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
He was - he was a man that could talk to anybody. Yes, he could talk to anybody. Anybody. Any class or anybody, he was always at home with them all you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Would you have been able to take worries to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
Well I think so. I think so. I never took any worries or mentioned anything to him - until I'd been married some years. But after my mother died he used to come and - to my house a lot, and we could always sit and talk about things. And - whether it was -
 being matured that made us like that - I don't know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 If you had something on your mind when you were little would you have talked to the other children about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Oh yes - well, my brother and I were always good pals. And the youngest girl and 
me, being in the same kind of work together, used to go to work together and go to London together, 'cos we used to go to London, and I was a good drawer and if she saw a hat - in a shop that was exclusive, I used to stand and draw it from the street and 
t
hey'd come and take it out of the window. And that sort of thing, yes, and so me and my youngest sister, we used to go to shows and then all the way to work we'd sing the shows and - kid ourselves - we was the actresses, and my oldest sister, we used to g
o
 - I used to go backwards and forwards to work with her, but she was always very - prim and proper. And - there was lots of things you couldn't say to her, but now we're older - she comes here regularly and we talk about everything and anything. It's just
 that I think we've always been on the - shy side you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did your parents expect you to behave towards them in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 We'd always got to respect them, yes. But never to the limit of being - nasty to us you know, were never nasty. The o
nly time my father ever got nasty - was if me or my sister quarrel}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
ed, which we - were inclined to do sometimes over our clothes. Because my mother used to dress us alike, and she was very dark, I was very fair, and now and again she'd get hold of my cloth
es, and I wouldn't have that, and I used to say, she's got my - dress, or she's got my so and so. My father used to say, have you? And she used to say, no I haven't, I've got me own. I used to say, no you haven't And he used to say, well now you go in the
re, and you go in there until you've sorted it out. And - you couldn't - he wouldn't let you quarrel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did they say that you should hit back or not if another child hit you or hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 No, I don't think they used to like the idea of - fighting be
cause - we did used to have one or two girls at school that were a bit spiteful, we did used to go home and tell mum about that. And she used to say, well don't - you know, don't mix with them. No. And any of our friends my mother used to sleep them, feed
 
them, make things for them and do anything for all my friends we all could always take all our friends home. Up in the bedrooms, anywhere and they could stop and sleep, providing the mother was - knew, and - like we was always friendly with the parents, y
o
u see, and - I've got a friend now I was going to her house tomorrow but she's got to go in - into hospital in the morning, but I was going to her house tomorrow, we've been friends ever since we was little kids, my dad used to make her shoes, because she
 
was jealous of my shoes, and - they were really more comfortable than we were, and her mother used to pay to have shoes made for - her, like mine, and if I had a dress done with blue on it, my mother had to make her a dress with pink on it. If she had her
 
hair in curls I had mine in curls. We used to go for our - pinafores, to pretend they'd been to the laundry you know, 'cos they was all crinkled and done up, and me and my friend used to work together like that. And if her father, he was a - a bandleader 
for the Luton band, bandmaster, and if they used to go, which they did, to Paris and London and places like that for trips, my mother'd always have my friend to sleep with us, for the weekend, 'til - like that you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What sort of people do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Well - I always think they'd - they hoped that we would marry - someone - very nice you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did they bring you up to consider that certain things were important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What sort of things did they think were important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Well - cleanliness and discipline and - truthfulness, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What did they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Well - they never used to swear, and I remember once when I was young I did swear. I can't even remember w
hat it was because I'm not a swearing person, although nowadays - it wouldn't worry me if I did say a wicked word. In fact I think I'd enjoy it. But in those - days, what did I say now. Either dammit or some such thing, and my father said, that's quite en
ough of that talk. He wouldn't have any -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 When grown ups were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes, I think so, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Well, I think they would have shrunk in the ground. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did they punish you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 No, I don't think so, no. No. Don't remember any of us ever doing anything that - really - upset them you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What if you were naughty like children are naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes. I remember my mother - givin
g my brother a good hiding. Because - being a boy - she seemed to love him more than she loved all us three girls put together. But - he was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120 mischievous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120  when he was young, and he's turned out to be very clever, and I think his mischief a lot of it was - in
 his research mind you know, and - always remember someone saying - coming and telling my mother one teatime that my brother had thrown his cap - took a boys cap off and thrown it - somewhere. And my mother gave my brother a good hiding. She shut him up i
n
 the bedroom, said, and you can stop up there for the rest of the night. She said, and I'll teach you to - you know, not to do things like that. About an hour afterwards, she says, oh dear, she said, I wish I hadn't hit him. She said, how do I know whethe
r
 he did do it or whether he didn't, and she said, if he did, she said, perhaps they did the same thing to him. I'll go up and see if he's all right. She goes upstairs and he was missing. He'd got out of the bedroom window, climbed onto the slates and was 
sitting on the doorstep whistling. There was my mother in tears. 'Cos she'd walloped him. She said, I'll never wallop him for anyone else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 So he didn't care about being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Well, I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did you girls ever get a smack?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 I think they w
ould have smacked us, you know, I don't ever remember. I remember my father having a brush in his hand once and I was afraid he was going to hit me with it, but he didn't. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Would you say that you got your ideas of how to behave and things from both parents, or one or other of them particularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 From both of them. Both of them. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 When you had a birthday would it have been different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes, we always had a little party, and the school}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1133596\charrsid14287120  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 friends used to come and - bring their little presents and things, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 You had special things to eat did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes, she used to make - trifles you know and - things. Cakes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did you have presents from your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes, we always had some little thing. I don't
 think they could ever afford a - a lot. But we'd perhaps have - well might be a new doll or - I was always for dressmaking, and she'd probably buy me a yard of material and some lace to make something for me doll, you know, or something like that. Father
 
always buy - bought - bought me paints, 'cos I used to paint. And - he used to say if I didn't go out at nights or if I didn't do this or didn't do the other he'd buy me some new paints, which he knew I was always wanting you know, so of course we used to
 
- bribe each other like that you know. Oh yes, he bought me many - many a thing - to sort of - I think it was to keep us on the right road if you know what I mean. You know. And - he'd always take our part. Yes, because when I was courting, and - I was ab
o
ut nineteen, and my father said to us that - could you do with a walk tonight, he said, with you and my young man then, take these shoes home. Which were long long way from home. We had to go through this park I'm telling you about, Peoples Park, I don't 
k
now if you know it, thought the Peoples Park, down the meadow, right through this way into Dunstable Road, to deliver these shoes, and it was to the manager of a big - dying place. Yes, we said we'd go, thrilled to bits to take these shoes, you know, the 
m
an always give us either - sixpence or a shilling or something you know when we got there. And going back - we stopped to have a little cuddle in the top of the park, and there was some man crawling - in the bushes. Well of course I've never experience an
y
thing like that before. And I don't think my boyfriend had. Anyway, he kicked out, but he didn't kick, the man, and we walked home. So of course when we got home my dad said, did you have a nice walk? So we said, yes. So we sat down and he said, what's wr
o
ng? I said, nothing. He said, something wrong. I said, there isn't. And my boy said, I - my boy said, I'll tell you. He said - some man was creeping about, he said, and it's upset her. So he said to my boy - didn't you give him a jolly good hiding, 'cos h
e }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4594632\charrsid14287120 said}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
 I would have done. He said, we - we - we've been just in the same position when we were young, he said, you've go to - but we weren't ever warned about anything like that, it was just - you know, something that, you know, upset us like, seeing him cr
awling - crawling along, we could hear the - hear somebody crawling along, and - we had a laugh about that and I - I thought to myself then, good old dad, he's stuck up for us you know. You could tell him anything like that. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did you have anything special about Christmas, was Christmas made much of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
Yes, but we - they never had a lot of money but we always had - always - all of us hung our stocking up, or a pillowcase, and we always had something you know. Didn't used to be the expensive prese
nts then. I prob - probably have a new doll, or a new - some books, writing books or painting books or something and always fruit and nuts, and probably a - shilling, you know something like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did you have anything special to eat on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
Oh yes. Yes. Used to have lovely Christmas - turkey and - suckling pigs. You could buy a sucking pig for a pound. When we were young. And they - they used to put them in the windows, little sucking pigs about as long as that with an orange in the m
outh, and you could buy the whole thing, and we used to have to take it to the bakers to be cooked, in the big ovens at the bakers. And the turkeys, used to have some walloping great turkeys. Then we always had rabbit pies at night you know, and hot veget
a
bles, hot plum pudding and - custard and that, yes. Ten and eleven at night. And our parties used to go on until about - two in the morning, all the aunts and cousins and uncles and - everyone used to come. And then we all used to walk across the top of t
h
e park, taking each other home. You'd take so and so home, singing all the way, arm in arm. And - I think my mother used to stop at home and clear up, father used to come with us. And all us boys and girls you know, used to be ever such fun, but of course
 there's nothing like that now. It's all you hire a cab, you know. You hire a cab if you're late and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did you have any musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes, we had a piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Who played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 And - well - my oldest sister had lessons, I wan
ted lessons, I think I've been - my brother and I were the two most musical in the family. But - as my sister had her lessons I used to play - by ear - what she was taught. So my mother thought I didn't need lessons. We used to go to the theatre, my pal a
n
d I, and both of us used to come home to my house, my friend'd sit and pick a tune out, then I'd pick a tune out, then we'd put the words together 'til we got the song and we was away. Yes. But my sister, she had to - go to a teacher, and she could only r
e
ad it off of a book. She'd got to learn it properly you see. I was always so cross because my mother always says you don't need to have lessons. But I think if I'd have had lessons then, I would have made a good pianist. I've had a piano right until a few
 
weeks ago I've only just sold it. I wanted a new bed and bedding so I sold me piano, and when I was ill I had to have me bed downstairs, and so I've got rid of it for the room as much as anything, and I've bought some new bedding with the money. So that's
 put an end to that. I've always had a piano of me own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did your parents play games with you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What sort of games did you play?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Used to have table tennis and - pinning the donkey's tail on on the wall and - ludo and snakes 
and ladders, all things like that, bingo and - all sorts of things, yes, always plenty of games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Would that be just at special times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 I think it was any time that we was at a loose end you know. They'd come out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What about books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
We had - well - people didn't buy books when we were young like they do now. And the one - the libraries, but we used to - I used to love - drawing, I used to have a lot of drawing books, and writing books. I used to kid meself when I was young th
at I was going to be a writer, and I used to sit and write little stories you know to meself, never show anyone. And writer little pieces of poetry. I used to write little songs, and all sorts of things, yes. But my brother, in the end - because they woul
dn't buy him a fiddle - or anything like that, made himself one. Yes, yes. He made himself a - one string fiddle to start with, and then he - made himself a - violin - well I don't know whether you'd call it a - a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid4594632\charrsid14287120 ukulele}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 , it was a thing like that you know,
 taught himself to play by ear. Yes. Yes. And then he was one of the first ones to - start experimenting with wireless. He was about the second one in Luton to have }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4594632\charrsid14287120 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 ireless. And you see you being young, you've never known what it is to be without your wir
eless. When we was young there was no such thing as wireless, when it first came out - we used to sit in our house with a cup or a basin on my mother's piano, with a little thing put in for - loudspeaker, we all sat round listening while my brother fiddle
d
 about with a little piece of wire, cats whiskers and things and it used to come through. We all used to jump up and cheer. And - in about 19 - I think it'd be about 1920 or something like that, he used to go and give demonstrations, put up a tent - in a 
c
hurch garden or somewhere and all the people used to come to listen. Yes, and he had a - an experimental licence. In the end he made no end of - wirelesses. Mm. He is a clever chap. A lovely painter too. Mm. He used to - he's been retired about two years,
 
and he's painted all his life for the love of painting, and now, he can - he could sell more pictures than he can paint, if he could - if he could do them. Mm. And from exhibitions, it's not private. Mm. Puts them in exhibitions, you've got to put the pri
c
e on, they just go. Mm. Well - he don't do a lot of it because he likes to get out, he says he's worked had and - he's not going to make himself a slave to anything. He's got a wife that's not too good in health and he takes her out - a lot, they go - fis
hing you know and - photographing, he's - always been a photographer you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Do you remember seeing your mother and father reading books when you were little at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes. And hiding them, they used to hide them. Yes, and it was only when we got
 older that we realized that - cheeky books - in them days people used to get them somehow, I don't say dirty books - but always remember finding a book in my mother's wardrobe when we were nosing about once, and she said, now she said, you should mind yo
u
r own business. And it worried me to death until I found out what the book was and what it was about. And it was only a cheeky love story, but in those days it was - something a bit - you know - oh yes. And I daresay she used to read them, then my father 
did, and they'd probably have a laugh about it and we - weren't supposed to know a thing about them you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 How about newspapers and magazines?
