had an early dinner, and we'd arrive there in about an hour and a half, and then we'd have a slap up tea, my grandmother always - was always prepared you know, she'd got all the others as well as us. Yes. And - kids galore.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did you enjoy that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 O
h lovely. I had a lovely grandma and grandad. They were poor but - ever so cosy. Yes, if it was cold there was always lovely soup ready for you and - pudding or - tart, jam tarts that she'd made the jam, and made the tarts you know. Could always rely on a
 - on something nice. And on the other hand we used to take her things that she couldn't afford or get, such as she did like a nice haddock and a new laid egg, and we used to take her things like that you know. And - but it was just that - it was -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 So you saw quite a lot of her?
