n the early days you know before all these big stores and shops were open, and they used to have these little oil lamps at the side you know, and there was the fish, the curtains, the fruit - and my mother always used to buy all her fruit Saturday afterno
on and evenings. You could get seven oranges for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4594632\charrsid14287120 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120  three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4594632\charrsid14287120 
 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 pence, big ones. And twenty-four for sixpence - smaller ones. And -
