o come selling pegs and - and lace and - different things you know. And tinkers used to call, in those days there were none of these beautiful - you know the sort of kettles we have now, and electric ones are super but I mean even before that, you remembe
r
 when we had - iron or tin kettles, you know, that you put on the gas, well before that - people used to have a kettle, they used to cost sixpence ha'penny, and you'd have a man come round two or three times during the year that would stand and solder it 
-
 for about tuppence, and - people - that's how people used to be because there weren't anything any different, apart from a big - iron kettle that was always on the open - fire, you'd always got a big iron kettle on the open fire for - you know, huge it w
as. But these tinkers used to come round -
