rs where you - got the little fire underneath and you tucked everything up and - lit them and away they went you know and - used to boil away there. She used to do that for our baths and everything, always light the copper. 'Cos you get about - twenty gal
lons of water you know with those huge - coppers. Yes. You don't see them very often now, they've still got one next door in their house, mm.
