own the hills. Yes. It was all when we was kids all outdoor fun, and everyone used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What did you do, you all took an orange and rolled it down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 I believe they used to buy them up there because there were - hundreds and thousands of oranges a
nd things about in those days for next to nothing. We've had - I - I've known my sister buy seven oranges and take to bed with her, she's had them side of her bed and eaten seven before she's gone to sleep. Yes. I mean who'd do that these days. You get an
 orange you think you're lucky don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did a lot of people do this orange rolling?
