Only to Harpenden. I used to go to Harpenden every - every summer for a month. Mm. To stay with me grandmother, yes. Used to have a lovely time. Because she lived on the main road, it was only a cottage like this, and - she lived on the main
 road and I used to have the front bedroom and the - huntsmen and the hounds used to come by at five in the morning, you know, with the bugles and things, you've never seen anything like that, you might in the country. Yes. We don't. And I've never seen a
nything like that since I've been young - since I was young. And then we used to go -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 You used to go for a month did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes, I used to go for a month.
