\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 No, it was mostly always me, I don't know why. A
nd I always remember my mother used to - make me go to the pork butchers and get a pound and a half of home made lard, to take with me. And I used to have to take this lard with me, on the train, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did you travel alone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Yes. Yes. And I - my 
mother always used to take me and put me on the train. And - I believe - yes, at that time my grandmother used to live, you know, quite close to the railway. And - then she moved up to what they call Old Bell. And when she moved up there we used to a- of 
course I used to make friends with her neighbours, and the girls and the boys which I still see some of them, after all these years, very rare but - if I do, if ever we meet in a caf\'e9
, there's no end to the fun we have going over old times. We used to go an
d pick blackberries, and crab apples and take them home then my grandmother used to light - a fire in her garden, and give us one of these gret old pots that she'd got to make the jam, and then she'd - she'd see that we made it properly and she'd give us 
clean jars to put it in, and then we'd have jam for tea, or she'd make us jam tarts, and we used to bring some home, we used to love that. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Something that you didn't do at home wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Well, my mother always used to make jam, I've made jam 
- as long as ever I can remember. But - we did have - we did have some fun like that when we were kiddies, and where all these lovely homes are now used to be open fields with horses, and we used to go riding on the back of these horses. And I loved it un
til one day one of 'em picked me up and - threw me over - by me - pinafore dress, that put me off of horses. Put me off of horses for life that did, it did, mm.
\par 
