 like that for a week. And we used to have an aunt come and stay with us, and then my brother sometimes used to go - to an aunt for a week or two, because I remember it was about two miles from where we lived, and he came walking home about four o'clock o
ne morning. He said, I want my mum. And he'd come out of her house, all the way through the town, and up to our house, I don't think he was above two or three. And my mother said never - you shall never go away again.
