le could easily move. And they all - they always had the chance. My father had the chance to buy property. He'd got an old fellow that used to come and sit and talk to him and he used to say, there's a couple of houses going Jake, you have one and I'll ha
v
e the other. He'd buy the two. And he died worth thousands of pounds. And I've known him - try to egg and kid my father - to put a few bob on these houses, but I don't think my father could foresee - this other man must have - well - these property dealer
s have got something haven't they that other people haven't. And he was not a smart man. Very shabbily dressed, humb}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12656273\charrsid14287120 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 
e type of man, and he married a woman about twenty years older than him, you'd have thought she was his mother, and he was kindness itself t
o her, and she was a lovely cook and looked after him just like a mother would a son, and he used to come and sit in my dad's shop - and talk to him, and my dad could have owed - rows - owned rows of houses if he could have talked him into it. But he woul
d
n't - my father wouldn't - easily be swayed. The chance was there. And I've had the same chances, and not taken them. I've always slipped up, if there's anything - where it's making money or doing anything, if it's doing it for nothing, I've done it, done
 
it well, done a good job, and been praised for it, nothing to see for it. And I had the chance to do things and take the jobs - that I've not taken, either my parents have stopped me because they were going - because it would mean me going away, or it was
 
me hadn't got the confidence to - to think I was good enough to do it. I could have had - I've had jobs offered me - over the years, time and time again, that if only I'd have had the pluck, and the nerve and the cheek to have - just taken it, I believe I
 could have made much better than the people that did actually do it. Yes. And so I - always blame meself for that you know, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Do you think that people used to go down in social class as well as going up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 No. No, I think people used to - people that had any idea of getting on got on. Because I remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 But if you got somebody who was worthless and lost all his money would he then slip down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3765441 EP  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 What were the reasons mostly for people coming down in the world as it were?
