Oh I remember rough music in my teens, in the first world war. Oh yes. Yes. And the - person used to work under me. Yes, oh yes. She worked under me all day. She - she used to have the officers there at night. An
d she'd got a husband, she'd got a lovely husband and - I think it was three or four children, and - she was a lovely looking woman. She used to have these officers there. And the people used to stand outside with tin cans, and chant and sing. Yes. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12656273\charrsid14287120 Yes, oh yes, rough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120  music, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1580481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3367996\charrsid14287120 Did she move in the end?
